' PlantUML example — Implementation layer: internal service call sequence for
' order placement inside APPLICATION-OMS-1.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/elements/03_application/applications/APPLICATION-OMS-1.yaml
'       "Core system for order lifecycle management" — single application boundary.
'   - canon/elements/02_business/processes/PROCESS-ORD-FULFILL-1.yaml
'       STEP-ORD-FULFILL-1 (startEvent) / STEP-ORD-FULFILL-2 ("Validate Order").
'
' Not a duplicate of canon/views/sequence/order-erasure-interaction.sequence.md:
' that Mermaid view shows OMS <-> CRM at the application-integration level (who
' talks to whom). This diagram opens up APPLICATION-OMS-1 itself and shows the
' internal service calls behind STEP-ORD-FULFILL-1/2 — detail no Transitrix
' notation captures, since elements model applications as a single boundary.

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml Order placement — OMS internal sequence

actor Customer #e8f2f5
participant "Order Service" as OS #e8f2f5
participant "Payment Service" as PS #e8f2f5
participant "Inventory Service" as IS #e8f2f5

note over Customer,IS: Inside APPLICATION-OMS-1 — STEP-ORD-FULFILL-1 / STEP-ORD-FULFILL-2

Customer -> OS : Place order
OS -> PS : Authorise payment
PS --> OS : Payment authorised
OS -> IS : Reserve stock
IS --> OS : Stock reserved
OS --> Customer : Order confirmed (Received)

@enduml
